comment:
In Narcissistic Abuse, the Abuser *ALWAYS* claims to be the victim.  They will then accuse their victim of doing to them everything that they, themselves did.  It is called "Gaslighting", and it is a secondary form of Abuse.  So, what we have are two people claiming abuse.  It is not difficult to tell which is the Abuser and which is the Victim.  The Narcissistic Abuser compulsively lies.  They claim to be perfect, don't drink or do drugs, even if there is proof that they do. They will also claim excessive abuse, but will have suffered no injuries.  They won't have had to seek hospital treatment.  The Abuser will have no physical evidence of abuse, they will expect you to take their word for it.  

The Victim will admit to having flaws.  They will tell the same story of abuse repeatedly, without the need to embellish it, or change details.  They will have had hospital treatment for injuries.  They will possess physical evidence.

The Victim is the one who hides, and the Abuser is the one desperately trying to find them, banging on the doors of rooms where their Victim has retreated from the abuse.  The Victim leaves at the first sign of violence.  The Narcissistic Abuser will name-call, belittle and berate them for leaving.  The Victim never taunts the Abuser, because that will escalate the violence.  

The Abuser tries to make the Victim feel as if it is all THEIR fault, they will isolate their Victim from their friends, and surround their Victim with their OWN friends, often persuade the Victim to take medication.  The Narcissistic Abuser always believes that they are the smartest person in the room.  That is their downfall.  Eventually their ridiculous claims of beatings and injuries will spiral out of control... they will be claiming injuries severe enough to maim or kill, but they will have treated it themselves, and have completely recovered.  There is a reason that prisons are filled with Narcissists.  They believe that they can get away with anything.  They have great disdain for Law Enforcement.  They always get caught.
